##$pgv_lang["google_analytics_help"]			= "~#pgv_lang[google_analytics]#~<br /><br />The #pgv_lang[google_analytics]# service is described in this <a href='http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_Analytics' target='_blank' title='Google Analytics'>Wikipedia article</a>.<br /><br />Please note that, if you choose to use this service, Google acquires the rights to all data it collects about visitor activity on your site.";
##$pgv_lang["USE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[USE_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS]#~<br /><br />Select <b>#pgv_lang[yes]#</b> to enable tracking of activity on your site by the #pgv_lang[google_analytics]# service.  You must subscribe to this service before you enable this option.";
##$pgv_lang["PGV_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[PGV_GOOGLE_ANALYTICS]#~<br /><br />Enter the account number assigned to your site when you subscribed to the #pgv_lang[google_analytics]# service.  This account number has the format <b>UA-xxxxxx-x</b>.";
##$pgv_lang["piwik_analytics_help"]			= "~#pgv_lang[piwik_analytics]#~<br /><br />The #pgv_lang[piwik_analytics]# open-source project is described <a href='http://piwik.org/' target='_blank' title='Piwik official web site'>here</a>.<br /><br />Piwik is an alternative to #pgv_lang[google_analytics]# that eliminates many of the privacy concerns.  You can install the Piwik application on your own web server or in your own domain, thus ensuring that you have complete control over the activity data that has been collected.";
##$pgv_lang["USE_PIWIK_ANALYTICS_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[USE_PIWIK_ANALYTICS]#~<br /><br />Select <b>#pgv_lang[yes]#</b> to enable tracking of activity on your site by a #pgv_lang[piwik_analytics]# server.  Your PhpGedView site must be registered on a Piwik server.";
##$pgv_lang["PGV_PIWIK_URL_help"]				= "~#pgv_lang[PGV_PIWIK_URL]#~<br /><br />Enter the URL to a Piwik server where your PhpGedView site is registered.";
##$pgv_lang["PGV_PIWIK_SITE_help"]			= "~#pgv_lang[PGV_PIWIK_SITE]#~<br /><br />Enter the numeric site ID assigned to your PhpGedView site by the Piwik server.";
##$pgv_lang["clustrmaps_analytics_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[clustrmaps_analytics]#~<br /><br />ClustrMaps is a combined hit counter, visitor tracker and geographic visualization tool.<br /><br />Each page includes a thumbnail map image generated by ClustrMaps.  When that image loads, a counter on the ClustrMaps site is incremented.  When the map, which is visible to all your visitors, is updated (daily, weekly, or monthly, depending on your traffic) it shows the locations of all the visitors to your page since the beginning of a specific time interval.<br /><br />If you have paid for the #pgv_lang[clustrmaps_analytics]# service, clicking on that thumbnail map image reveals a larger world map display.<br /><br />More details are available on the <a href='http://www.clustrmaps.com/' target='_blank' title='ClustrMaps site'>ClustrMaps site</a>.";
##$pgv_lang["USE_CLUSTRMAPS_ANALYTICS_help"]	= "~#pgv_lang[USE_CLUSTRMAPS_ANALYTICS]#~<br /><br />Select <b>#pgv_lang[yes]#</b> to enable tracking of activity on your site by a #pgv_lang[clustrmaps_analytics]# server.";
##$pgv_lang["PGV_CLUSTRMAPS_SITE_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[PGV_CLUSTRMAPS_SITE]#~<br /><br />Enter the URL of your PhpGedView site.  This value has been filled in for you, and you would not normally need to change it.";
##$pgv_lang["PGV_CLUSTRMAPS_SERVER_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[PGV_CLUSTRMAPS_SERVER]#~<br /><br />Enter the server number assigned by the #pgv_lang[clustrmaps_analytics]# service when you activated your account.";

##$pgv_lang["SHOW_LIST_PLACES"]	= "Place levels to show on lists";
##$pgv_lang["SHOW_LIST_PLACES_help"]	= "~#pgv_lang[SHOW_LIST_PLACES]#~<br /><br />This determines how much of the Place information is shown in the Place fields on lists.<br /><br />Setting the value to <b>9</b> will ensure that all Place information will be shown.  Setting the value to <b>0</b> (zero) will hide places completely.  Setting the value to <b>1</b> will show the topmost level, which is normally the country.  Setting it to <b>2</b> will show the topmost two levels.  The second topmost level, below the country, is often the state, province, or territory. Etc.<br />";

$pgv_lang["new_gedcom_title"]		= "Genealogie z [#GEDCOMFILE#]";
##$pgv_lang["keep_media_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[keep_media]#~<br /><br />Should existing media links be retained in the database when a replacement GEDCOM is being uploaded. The <b>No</b> option removes existing media links from the database, while the <b>Yes</b> option keeps them.<br /><br />This option is useful when you export your GEDCOM from PhpGedView to an off-line GEDCOM maintenance program that does not handle embedded media pointers properly, and then subsequently re-import that changed GEDCOM into PhpGedView.  Under such circumstances, the media pointers within the GEDCOM you exported to your off-line editing program are destroyed, and you would have to re-link all of your media files to the proper Person, Family, and Source records after you re-import the GEDCOM into PhpGedView.<br /><br />The <b>Yes</b> option tells PhpGedView to keep the existing media links so that you do not have to re-create them after you import the changed GEDCOM, but this requires the off-line editing program to always produce the same Person, Family, and Source identification numbers.<br /><br /><i>Family Tree Maker</i> is one of several off-line editing programs that does <u>not</u> properly handle media object pointers within the GEDCOM.  <i>Legacy</i>, among many others, <u>does</u> handle these properly.<br />";
##$pgv_lang["USE_MEDIA_VIEWER"]			= "Use Media Viewer";
##$pgv_lang["USE_MEDIA_VIEWER_help"]		= "~#pgv_lang[USE_MEDIA_VIEWER]#~<br /><br />When this option is <b>#pgv_lang[yes]#</b>, clicking on images will produce the Media Viewer page.  This page shows the details of the image.  If you have sufficient rights, you can also edit these details.<br /><br />When this option is <b>#pgv_lang[no]#</b>, clicking on images will produce a full-size image in a new window.<br />";
